units metal 
boundary        p p p
atom_style      atomic
read_data       relaxed_G_H.data #<- name your relaxed (optimised) graphene +H structure here.
#read_restart	restart.eql

#Force fields: I changed these to the same as optimise-test
pair_style airebo 3.0 1 0 
pair_coeff * * CH.airebo C H

#Anneal part of the code, using NVT ensemble

thermo 1
thermo_style custom step temp ke pe etotal fmax

fix 1 all nvt temp 10.0 300.0 0.2 #<- this sets temperature to ramp up slowly from 10 K to 300 K in a step of 0.2. You can test changing the ramping value to see how it affects the ramping speed. Also you can read more tips about this in the lammps manual by searching the command "fix nvt".

velocity all create 10.0 196419822 dist uniform # <- this sets the initial velocity giving total temperature of 10 K to atoms randomly 

dump 1 all xyz 100 coord-out300.xyz # <- dump xyz frames every 2000 steps, you should test this with a small run, see how many steps you can skip and still see resonable dynamics
dump_modify 1 element C H

timestep 0.0002  #so 20 picosec per 100 000 steps
run 2500000  # <- this sets total run time at 1 000 000 x timestep. The "units metal" at the top sets the units for the simulation, for which time is given in picoseconds. Test with shorter run.

write_restart restart.eql  # <- this prints out a restart file, that you can use to continue the run from where it stopped by giving it to the code in the place of your optimised structure. Just change the command read_data into read_restart.

